---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = '/personal-site';
---

<Layout title="Blog | Ela Sobol">
  <main style="max-width: 850px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 4rem 2rem;">
    <h1 style="color: #1565c0; font-size: 3rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">Blog</h1>
    
    <article style="padding: 2.5rem; background: #fff0f5; border-radius: 20px; box-shadow: 0 4px 15px rgba(0,0,0,0.05); border: 1px solid rgba(194, 24, 91, 0.05);">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0; color: #ad1457; font-size: 1.8rem;">Postcards from Cambridge: A Summer of History & Psychology</h2>
      <p style="color: #666; font-style: italic; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">March 6, 2026 • 5 min read</p>
      
      <p style="font-size: 1.1rem; line-height: 1.7; color: #444;">
        This past summer, I had the incredible opportunity of studying abroad in Cambridge, England for 5 weeks. 
        Between advanced psychology electives and exploring the historic halls of Christ’s College, it was an experience I'll never forget...
      </p>
      
      <a href={`${base}/blog/cambridge`} style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 1rem; color: #ad1457; font-weight: bold; text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid #ad1457; padding-bottom: 2px;">
        Read More →
      </a>
    </article>
  </main>
</Layout>
